Baby elephant is a 'mascot' at Marina Phuket Resort in Thailand . 
  Jaime Singleton saw the baby elephant tied to a pole outside a restaurant in December . 
  She launched a petition to have it freed . 
  The petition has received 50,627 signatures and the target is 75,000 . 
  The baby elephant is forced to perform tricks for guests and is also used in weddings . 
  It comes after another resort in Thailand posted a picture of a drunken guest riding an elephant . 
  Ms Singleton said the elephants are not owned by the resort but are 'rented out' by private companies . 
  She said the animal is called Nadia and is tied up outside the restaurant . 
